title: Fixed fp.pinrow6, fp.pinrow6-female, femaleHeader, femaleHeader2 and pinRow examples
description: Fixes rendering crashes caused by nonstandard shape strings and diameter property names in the FootprintPlatedHole component.
body: /fix #165 /fix #166 /fix #168 /fix #169 /fix #170 ## Summary Make `FootprintPlatedHole` tolerant of footprint generator variants that return nonstandard shape strings (e.g. `circular_hole_with_rect_pad`) and alternative diameter property names. This prevents crashes when rendering plated holes with nonstandard data formats. ### Details Some footprints produced by `@tscircuit/footprinter` (or other footprint sources) use unconventional shape identifiers and inconsistent property names for plated-hole diameters. For example, a hole might be described as `circular_hole_with_rect_pad` and define properties like `outerDiameter`, `holeDiameter`, or `diameter` instead of the expected `outer_diameter` and `hole_diameter`. Previously, this caused exceptions such as: Shape not supported: `circular_hole_with_rect_pad` which crashed the renderer in certain cases. ## Before ## After

title: refactor(pcb): Improve panel rendering and refactor numeric parsing
description: Adds support for rendering multi-board panels, refactors numeric parsing to use distance.parse, and fixes a bug in bounds calculation for polygon pads.
body:
This pull request introduces support for rendering multi-board panels, refactors numeric       
parsing to use distance.parse, and fixes a related bug in bounds calculation.                  

Key Changes:                                                                                   

 1 Multi-Board Panel Support:                                                                  
    • The SVG bounding box calculation in both PCB and solder paste mask renderers now         
      correctly includes pcb_panel elements, allowing panels with multiple boards to be        
      rendered properly.                                                                       
    • pcb_panel is no longer considered a board for board-specific boundary calculations, which
      improves logical consistency.                                                            
    • A new test case and snapshot have been added to verify the visual output of a multi-board
      panel.                                                                                   
 2 Refactor to distance.parse:                                                                 
    • The custom toNumeric helper function has been completely removed.                        
    • All numeric parsing of distance values now uses distance.parse from the circuit-json     
      library. This standardizes how distance units are handled and reduces maintenance.       
 3 Bug Fix:                                                                                    
    • Fixed a crash that occurred when calculating the bounds for pcb_smtpad elements with a   
      polygon shape. The bounds calculation logic was reordered to handle polygon pads         
      correctly, preventing an error from distance.parse receiving NaN values.

title: fix: the bug report reloads on every key press
description: Fixes the bug where typing in the bug report textarea causes the entire FileMenuLeftHeader to re-render on every keystroke by switching to uncontrolled input.
body:
## The Root Cause

  The issue was that typing in the bug report textarea was causing the entire FileMenuLeftHeader
  to re-render because:
  1. useBugReportDialog had state that changed on every keystroke (userText)
  2. This hook was called inside FileMenuLeftHeader
  3. Every state change triggered a re-render of the entire component tree

## Approach

Switch to uncontrolled input
